            <fr:title text="Composition of invertible maps › "><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003J.xml" title="Composition of invertible maps" addr="//erct/erct-003J" type="local">Composition of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">invertible</fr:link> maps</fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002C.xml" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" addr="//erct/erct-002C" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002C" /></fr:link>, it suffices to find a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000X.xml" title="Quasi-inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> to the composite <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f]]></fr:tex>; we take this to be the composite (<fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002L.xml" title="Composition of quasi-invertible maps" addr="//erct/erct-002L" type="local">Construction <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002L" /></fr:link>) of the underlying <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000X.xml" title="Quasi-inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverses</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
