            <fr:title text="Quasi-invertible maps are contractible › "><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002M.xml" title="Quasi-invertible maps are contractible" addr="//erct/erct-002M" type="local"><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000X.xml" title="Quasi-inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000X" type="local">Quasi-invertible</fr:link> maps are <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">contractible</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Any <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000X.xml" title="Quasi-inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002C.xml" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" addr="//erct/erct-002C" type="local">can be improved</fr:link> to a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">coherent inverse</fr:link>, and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">any coherently invertible map</fr:link> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
